Client Request
   ↓
Gateway Entry Point
   ↓
→ GatewayRoutingConfig (Match path → route)
   ↓
→ Global Filters (e.g., JWTAuthenticationFilter)
       ↓
   RouteValidator used inside Filter (secured vs open route)
       ↓
   Auth Service Call (JWT validate)
       ↓
→ Security Config Check (if using Spring Security at gateway)
       ↓
Request Forwarded to Target Microservice (user-service, order-service, etc.)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Client Request →
2. CorsGlobalConfiguration: Handle CORS →
3. GatewayRoutingConfig: Match route →
4. JwtAuthenticationFilter (GlobalFilter):
       └─ RouteValidator used inside it
       └─ Call auth-service to validate token →
5. GatewaySecurityConfig (if applicable): Authorize exchange →
6. Forward to Target Microservice (user-service, etc.)
